&lt;h2&gt;BANK OPPORTUNITY&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have some opportunities for Speech and Language Therapists with an interest in working with adults with acquired disorders to work on the bank for the SLT service. The adult community service works across Derby city and Derbyshire, we also have a Service Level Agreement to provide the service to Derby Hospitals. There are established and highly experienced SLTs working in these areas, with strong working relationships with the wider MDT. Our service is primarily delivered to adults in their settings; home, care home, local hospital and acute hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a large and dynamic Speech and Language Therapy service of around 100 staff working across all service areas in Derbyshire. We are looking for HCPC and RCSLT registered Speech and Language Therapists, with experience in a specialist area and established skills in dysphagia assessment and management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be proficient in your abilities to deliver high-quality, evidence-based practice, with assessment and therapeutic abilities, including dysphagia management in this specialist area. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will have a commitment to providing a high standard of patient-focused care and be a strong team player. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As a clinical employee it will be your responsibility to ensure that your behaviour and values reflect those set out in the DCHS Way.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lisa Salton&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SLT Service Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;lisa.salton@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
